2. Self-Cancellation Rule (a ^ a = 0):
   XORing a number with itself evaluates to 0. Therefore, every number that 
   appears an EVEN number of times completely cancels out to 0, leaving behind 
   only the numbers that appear an ODD number of times.

3. Rightmost Set Bit Concept (For finding two unique values):
   When two distinct numbers are left over in the XOR total sum, the resulting value 
